analysis.Summary: Vue 3 single-file component that renders an SVG icon depicting a 2×2 grid (catalog) with a customizable fill color.
analysis.Purpose: Provides a reusable IconCatalog component in the project’s icon library, allowing other UI pieces to display a catalog/grid icon with adjustable color.

Components.name: IconCatalog
responsibilities: Render an SVG graphic representing a catalog or grid icon.
Accept props for customizing the fill color and theme.

Functions.name: defineProps
Functions.purpose: Declare component props in the <script setup> context.

fill.description: Sets the SVG path fill color.

theme.description: Currently unused, reserved for theming contexts.

Dependencies: CSS custom properties (e.g. --black) for default coloring
analysis.Usage: Imported wherever an catalog/grid icon is needed: import IconCatalog from 'modules/icons/entities/IconCatalog.vue'; then use <IconCatalog :fill="'#ff0000'" /> in templates.
Notes: There is no <style> block – styles come from external CSS variables.
The 'theme' prop is defined but not applied in the template; may be reserved for future use or omitted.
SVG viewBox and dimensions are fixed at 27×27.
